Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Heat oil in 6-quart oven-proof baking dish or saucepan over high heat. Lightly brown both sides of chicken pieces in oil. Stir in remaining ingredients except spinach. Heat to boiling; cover. Bake 40 minutes. Stir in spinach; bake about 10 minutes longer or until juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.